'''Civil Movement "People's Self-Defense"''' ({{lang-uk|ÐÑÐ¾Ð¼Ð°Ð´ÑÐ½ÑÑÐºÐ¸Ð¹ ÑÑÑ Â«ÐÐ°ÑÐ¾Ð´Ð½Ð° ÑÐ°Ð¼Ð¾Ð¾Ð±Ð¾ÑÐ¾Ð½Ð°Â»}}) is a [[political movement]] in [[Ukraine]], headed by a former [[Socialist Party of Ukraine|SPU]] member [[Yuriy Lutsenko]].
==History==
{{Empty section|date=June 2010}} ==Possible dismantlement== In an interview with the Silski Visti (Village News) newspaper on 29 January 2009 Yuriy Lutsenko declared that "The People's Self-Defense as an insurgent, protesting, and not very structured civil movement has ceased to exist". Lutsenko also said he was planning to direct the organizational changes to the political party [[Forward, Ukraine!]].<ref>[http://www.interfax.com.ua/eng/main/6595/ Interior minister planning to set up full-fledged political force], [[Interfax|Interfax-Ukraine]] (29-01-2009)</ref> In April 2010 Forward, Ukraine! renamed itself [[People's Self-Defense Political Party]].<ref name=namegame>[http://www.kyivpost.com/news/politics/detail/64605/ Forward, Ukraine! Party changes name to People's Self-Defense], [[Kyiv Post]] (April 21, 2010)</ref> Lutsenko became leader of that party.<ref>[http://www.kyivpost.com/news/politics/detail/98630/print/ Prosecutor's office refuses to release Lutsenko on bail, says People's Self-Defense], [[Kyiv Post]] (March 1, 2011)</ref>
